claim.claim-text:
27. A method for shipping goods, said method comprising:
providing a coded information tag and a parcel to be shipped, said parcel including merchandise for delivery to a recipient;
writing information to said coded information tag in a format readable by said recipient, the format of at least a portion of said information being specified by said recipient, to indicate receipt of said goods, wherein said information describes said merchandise in an inventorying format of said recipient, and readable by said shipping service provider to track shipment of said parcel;
associating said coded information tag with said parcel; and
shipping said parcel and said coded information tag to said recipient.

34. A method for tracking inventory, said method comprising:
receiving a message linking coded information on a parcel to goods to be tracked in an inventory system, said goods being contained in said parcel;
shipping said parcel including said goods;
decoding said coded information by a shipping service provider for use in tracking shipment of said parcel including said goods;
receiving said parcel including said goods;
decoding said coded information by a recipient of said parcel including said goods; and
based on said decoding, updating a database in said inventory system to show receipt of said goods included in said parcel, wherein a format of at least a portion of said coded information is specified by said recipient.

45. The system of claim 44 wherein said shipping company comprises a service selected from the group comprising:
a government operated postal service;
a private package delivery service;
a global package delivery service;
a time-definite delivery service;
an overnight delivery service; or
a next day delivery service.
